<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Two main sections: Verse (bars 1-8, repeated) and Bridge (bars 9-17).
- Verse: V-IV-V7 and I-V-IV-V chord progressions. Half-note LH blocks for stability.
  V7(G7) in bar 1 beat 4 encoded with 7th (F3) in bass: G2-D3-F3-B3.
- Bridge opens with IV pickup (bar 9 pickup), then ascending melodic line reaches E5 (bar 10).
  Full per-beat LH at bridge to support the higher register melody.
- Bar 11: viiø7 (sub for Bm7) gives rich 4-note LH at bridge climax point.
- Bar 12: ii7 (sub for D7) with C in the LH creates "added 7th" color: D2-A2-C3-F3.
- Final convergence bars 14-17: I-iii-IV-I → V-IV-I-V → IV-I-ii-V → I.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- V7 in bar 1/5: F3 (the 7th) sits just above D3 in the LH — creates smooth step motion into
  the following IV (A3-F3→A3-F3 common tones).
- Bridge bar 10: LH bass I→vi→V→I = C2→A2→G2→C2 (descending 3rd then step, smooth).
- Bar 12 vi→V→vi→ii7 bass line: A2→G2→A2→D2 — a pendulum then leap of 5th.
- Common tone B3 held in LH between V and vii°7 (bar 11) — no repeated attack needed.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Sparse pickup → half-note blocks in verse → opening LH octave-5th only on pickup bar 4 →
  bridge builds to per-beat 4-voice LH in bar 10 (climax) →
  gradual thinning bars 13-15 → final root-pos I convergence bar 17.
-->
